data.name: nightLabel1.Text
data.value: This Full Body Workout Plan is designed for beginners looking to target all major muscle groups. It is a well-rounded routine that includes a variety of exercises to build strength, endurance, and overall fitness. Whether you're new to exercise or returning after a break, this workout will help you establish a solid foundation for your fitness journey.

data.name: nightLabel2.Text
data.value: The Push/Pull/Legs (PPL) Split Workout Plan is an intermediate-level routine that divides workouts into pushing muscles, pulling muscles, and leg muscles. This split allows for targeted training of specific muscle groups on different days, ensuring ample recovery time between sessions. By incorporating compound exercises and isolation movements, this plan aims to enhance muscle strength, endurance, and overall muscular balance.

data.name: nightLabel4.Text
data.value: The Justin's Split Workout Plan offers a versatile approach to training, targeting specific muscle groups on different days for balanced development and strength gains. This split combines focused muscle group sessions with a comprehensive full-body workout for a well-rounded fitness routine. Whether you're aiming to sculpt your arms, strengthen your core, or build leg endurance, this plan provides a mix of isolation and compound exercises to help you reach your fitness goals.

data.name: nightLabel6.Text
data.value: The Cardio Workout Plan is designed to improve cardiovascular fitness, endurance, and overall health. This plan incorporates a variety of cardio exercises to get your heart pumping and calories burning. Whether you prefer running, cycling, or high-intensity interval training (HIIT), this plan offers a range of options to suit your fitness level and goals.

data.name: nightLabel10.Text
data.value: The Upper/Lower Split Workout Plan is an intermediate-level routine that alternates between upper body and lower body workouts. This split allows for focused training of upper body muscles (chest, back, shoulders, arms) on one day and lower body muscles (quads, hamstrings, calves) on the next. By incorporating compound lifts and targeted exercises, this plan aims to improve strength, muscle definition, and overall fitness.
